<h2>Key factors that change solar ROI</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Electricity rates:</strong> Higher rates generally increase savings, but the impact depends on your usage.</li>
<li><strong>Sun exposure:</strong> Roof angle, shading, and regional sun hours all affect production.</li>
<li><strong>System size:</strong> Oversizing can reduce payback; undersizing may miss savings.</li>
<li><strong>Incentives:</strong> Federal, state, and utility programs change over time—verify current eligibility.</li>
<li><strong>Net metering:</strong> Policies vary by utility and can materially affect returns.</li>
</ul>
